MongoDB.

	- MongoDB is the ligth weigth DataBase Supports JSON.
	- As a Mongo Developer , we can Perform CRUD Operations on JSON.
	- MongoDB Follows the Client Server Architecture.

Start the Server.
-

>mongod
	- the above operable program used to start the Mongo Server.
	- in general mongoserver listening the Port No.27017.
	- mongo server follows the "mongo" protocol.

	Ex.
		mongo://localhost:27017 


Create the Client
-
>mongo
	- MongoClient Can Connect to Mongo Server.


MongoDB Opearations
-
1. show dbs;
	- it will show the available databases in mongodb.

2. use demo;
	- it will create and switches to demo database.

3. db.dropDatabase();
	- it will drop the database.(Current DataBase)

4. db.createCollection("emp");
	- emp collection will be created in mongodb.

5. db.emp.insert({'id':1,'name':'Hello_1','age':20});	
	- insert the JSON Object into collection.

6. db.emp.find();
	- We can Fetch the data from the Collection (emp)

7.db.emp.remove({});
     -remove a document from the collection.

8.show collections
     -You can check the created collection by using the command show collections.
	
9.db.mycollection.drop()
    -MongoDB's db.collection.drop() is used to drop a collection from the database.

10. db.emp.update({'id':1},{$set:{'name':'Hero','age':20}});





